test law 01   1:   LEX: «Paid Escrow».
test law 01   2:   LEXON: ‹0.3.xx›.
test law 01   3:   COMMENT: ‹%PRE %GEN %JUR an escrow that is controlled by a third party for a fee.›.

test law 01   5:   LAW: New York
test law 01   6:   “«Paying Party»” is a person.
test law 01   7:   “«Paid Party»” is a person.
test law 01   8:   “«Pay Master»” is a person.
test law 01   9:   “«Payment»” is an amount.
test law 01  10:   “«Payment Fee»” is an amount.
test law 01  11:   “«Non-Payment Fee»” is an amount.
test law 01  12:   “«Master's Fee»” is an amount.

test law 01  14:   The «Paying Party» pays a «Payment» into escrow,
test law 01  15:   appoints the «Paid Party»,
test law 01  16:   appoints the «Pay Master»,
test law 01  17:   and also fixes the «Master's Fee».

test law 01  19:   CLAUSE: «Make Payment».
test law 01  20:   The «Pay Master» may pay from escrow the «Master's Fee» to themselves,
test law 01  22:   and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the «Paid Party».

test law 01  24:   CLAUSE: «Return Payment».
test law 01  25:   The «Pay Master» may pay from escrow the «Non-Payment Fee» to themselves,
test law 01  27:   and afterwards return the remainder of the escrow to the «Paying Party».


